Crime scene tape [Courtesy]  A General Service Unit (GSU) officer based at Miteta Camp in Laikipia West shot his colleague following an argument yesterday afternoon  According to sources privy to the incident, the two officers had just finished having lunch together at the camp established to curb insecurity in the region.   Laikipia County Police Commander John Nyoike confirmed the incident, saying that the two were involved in an argument before the shooting.   "The suspect who is on the run shot his colleague killing him on the spot. He then vanished into nearby bushes in a valley leading towards Baringo County," said Mr Nyoike.   State okays Laikipia's Sh1b seven year bond  Laikipia, SG to partner on SME and innovation promotion  Stop the Laikipia killings  Bandits ambush and kill two police officers along Laikipia-Baringo border The police boss revealed that the suspect, whose identity was not immediately released, escaped with his loaded gun and a few of his belongings.   "He picked his gun and sped off while shooting in the air. Our officers are pursuing him," said Nyoike.      CS Fred Matiang'i says the Government is committed to addressing the insecurity in Laikipia County  Kamket Kizimbani: Mbunge wa Tiaty amekamatwa jana kuhusiana na mapigano eneo la Laikipia  Laikipia county Gov't enters into a lease agreement to enable it scale-up infrastructure development By Daniel Chege | 10 hours ago By Caroline Chebet | 10 hours ago By Julius Chepkwony | 10 hours ago By Kennedy Gachuhi | 19 hours ago Why Ruto wants Chief Justice Koome out of 2022 polls team